@startuml C4_Pattern_ServiceInvocation
!include https://raw.githubusercontent.com/plantuml-stdlib/C4-PlantUML/master/C4_Component.puml

title YAWL Workflow Pattern - External Service Invocation

Boundary(yawl_task, "YAWL Task") {
    Component(service_task, "ServiceTask", "Task", "Invoke external")
    Component(service_config, "ServiceConfig", "Config", "Endpoint URL")
}

Boundary(invocation, "Service Invocation") {
    Component(http_client, "HTTPClient", "Transport", "REST/SOAP")
    Component(request_builder, "RequestBuilder", "Builder", "Construct request")
    Component(response_handler, "ResponseHandler", "Parser", "Parse response")
    Component(error_handler, "ErrorHandler", "Errors", "Handle failures")
}

Boundary(external_service, "External Service") {
    Component(service_endpoint, "ServiceEndpoint", "API", "Remote service")
}

Boundary(resilience, "Resilience") {
    Component(circuit_breaker, "CircuitBreaker", "Pattern", "Fail fast")
    Component(retry, "RetryPolicy", "Backoff", "Retry on failure")
    Component(timeout, "TimeoutPolicy", "Limit", "Max wait time")
}

service_task --> service_config: Uses endpoint
service_config --> request_builder: Gets URL
request_builder --> http_client: Sends via
http_client --> service_endpoint: Invokes
service_endpoint --> response_handler: Returns response
response_handler --> service_task: Completes

error_handler --> circuit_breaker: Routes errors
circuit_breaker --> retry: Retries if safe
retry --> timeout: With timeout

Note as N1
Service Invocation:
1. Build request from task input
2. Send via HTTP/SOAP client
3. Parse response
4. Handle errors/retries
5. Return to YAWL

Timeout: <30 seconds default
Retry: Exponential backoff
End note

SHOW_LEGEND()
@enduml
